These are tools developed under the sponship of Beth Israel Hosptial, Boston Mass. The primary tool is the Pet-Ct Viewer for use with PET/SPECT and CT/MRI images. Fusion is done between the modalities to show the radioactive activity on top of the anotomical structure.

The primary source is located at [http://sourceforge.net/p/bifijiplugins/wiki/Pet-Ct%20Viewer/]. You may browse through the site and download from it.
